            <title><![CDATA[11 Great Games To Grab From PlayStation's 30th Anniversary Sale]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/playstation-sale-ps5-30th-anniversary-helldivers-2-ff7-1851711614</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/11-great-games-to-grab-from-playstations-30th-anniversary-sale.1050111/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/playstation-sale-ps5-30th-anniversary-helldivers-2-ff7-1851711614<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="0684f3557ab7cb0c57fe3b2699bf38b7" data-recommend-id="image://0684f3557ab7cb0c57fe3b2699bf38b7" data-format="png" data-width="1200" data-height="675" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A DualSense controller shows the original PS1 logo. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A DualSense controller shows the original PS1 logo. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sony</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="0684f3557ab7cb0c57fe3b2699bf38b7" data-recommend-id="image://0684f3557ab7cb0c57fe3b2699bf38b7" data-format="png" data-width="1200" data-height="675" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A DualSense controller shows the original PS1 logo. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>Sony’s big <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/playstation-psn-ps5-black-friday-deals-ps-plus-games-1851706224&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/playstation-psn-ps5-black-friday-deals-ps-plus-games-1851706224">Black Friday sale</a></span> has rolled into its <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/bloodborne-remake-ps5-60fps-sony-playstation-tga-2024-1851711314&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/bloodborne-remake-ps5-60fps-sony-playstation-tga-2024-1851711314">PlayStation 30th anniversary sale</a></span> without missing a beat. There are lots more games that are heavily discounted on PSN right now, from blockbuster PS5 exclusives to some equally amazing but lesser-known games that might not be on your radar. </p><p>You can currently get just about every major Sony first-party blockbuster from the last few years for around $30 or less. Here’s the full list to refresh your memory:</p><blockquote data-type="BlockQuote"><ul data-type="List" data-style="Bullet"><li><em>Helldivers 2 </em>- $31 (20 percent off)</li><li><em>Spider-Man 2 </em>- $40 (43 percent off)</li><li><em>God of War Ragnarok </em>- $30 (58 percent off)</li><li><em>Horizon Forbidden West: Complete Edition </em>- $40 (34 percent off)</li><li><em>Returnal </em>- $30 (58  percent off)<br></li><li><em>Ratchet and Clank Rift Apart Deluxe Edition </em>- $40 (50 percent off)</li><li><em>Ghost of Tsushima: Director’s Cut </em>- $30 (58 percent off)</li><li><em>Death Stranding: Director’s Cut </em>- $20 (60 percent off)</li><li><em>The Last of Us Part I </em>- $30 (58 percent off)</li><li><em>The Last of Us Part II </em>- $25 (30 percent off)</li><li><em>Spider-Man Miles Morales </em>- $20 (60 percent off)</li><li><em>Demon’s Souls Deluxe Edition </em>- $50 (45 percent off)</li></ul></blockquote><p>Weirdly, a couple of the games are only on sale for the deluxe editions. Also, <em>Spider-Man Remastered</em>&nbsp;is still full price at $50. The remaster of <em>Horizon Zero Dawn</em> also just came out so it’s still full price and you can no longer get the original PS4 version that was usually on sale for just $10. From the above list, <em>Death Stranding</em> and<em> Ghost of Tsushima </em>are good pickups since both have sequels out next year. </p><p>But there are also a bunch of other games on sale on PSN right now. You can click through the above slideshow for our other favorite picks. </p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="f36bf14d226337b17149b66852ed6f88" data-recommend-id="image://f36bf14d226337b17149b66852ed6f88" data-format="png" data-width="2724" data-height="1533" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Cloud looks at the Shinra office. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Cloud looks at the Shinra office. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Square Enix</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="f36bf14d226337b17149b66852ed6f88" data-recommend-id="image://f36bf14d226337b17149b66852ed6f88" data-format="png" data-width="2724" data-height="1533" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Cloud looks at the Shinra office. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>The original <em>Final Fantasy VII</em> <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/final-fantasy-7-ff7-review-1997-worth-playing-1851411735&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/final-fantasy-7-ff7-review-1997-worth-playing-1851411735">is still peak</a></span>. It’s also required playing for fully appreciating the recent remake trilogy, the first two games of which are also on sale right now. And unlike many modern RPGs, including <em>FFVII Rebirth</em>, you can cruise through the original 1997 PS1 game pretty quickly. The storytelling, music, and vibes are still immaculate. It’s one of the few proper ways to celebrate PlayStation’s latest milestone. </p><p><strong>Price:</strong> $6.40 (60 percent off)</p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="d51dd3a4866107adb7bcca78696d76f4" data-recommend-id="image://d51dd3a4866107adb7bcca78696d76f4" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Two Yakuza fight. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Two Yakuza fight. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sega</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="d51dd3a4866107adb7bcca78696d76f4" data-recommend-id="image://d51dd3a4866107adb7bcca78696d76f4" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Two Yakuza fight. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>The <em>Like a Dragon</em> series has recently hit a new gear with sprawling new entries every other year, plus there’s a live-action adaptation that just hit Amazon Prime Video. If you really want to get <em>Yakuza/Like a Dragon</em>-pilled and don’t know where to start, though, <em>Yakuza 0</em>, a prequel to the first game with all of the series’ modern refinements, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/you-really-need-to-play-the-yakuza-games-1747406314&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/you-really-need-to-play-the-yakuza-games-1747406314">is still you’re best bet</a></span>. </p><p><strong>Price:</strong> $11 (45 percent off)</p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="b19171676d4a851ba033b052ba2c6e53" data-recommend-id="image://b19171676d4a851ba033b052ba2c6e53" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A hitman takes aim at an F1 race. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A hitman takes aim at an F1 race. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->IO Interactive</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="b19171676d4a851ba033b052ba2c6e53" data-recommend-id="image://b19171676d4a851ba033b052ba2c6e53" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A hitman takes aim at an F1 race. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p><em>Hitman World of Assassination</em> <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/hitman-3-world-assassination-dlc-delisted-steam-io-1849945934&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/hitman-3-world-assassination-dlc-delisted-steam-io-1849945934">is a wild achievement</a></span>. It effectively turns the game into a platform, bringing over all the levels of the first two games in the recent trilogy and putting them inside of <em>Hitman 3</em>. Plus, there’s an entire new roguelike mode that is worth the price of admission alone. It’s probably still the benchmark for immersive stealth games. </p><p><strong>Price:</strong> $28 (60 percent off)</p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="15e138a339d6e8238a545af61dd42ea2" data-recommend-id="image://15e138a339d6e8238a545af61dd42ea2" data-format="png" data-width="2000" data-height="1125" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Penny's Big Breakaway. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Penny's Big Breakaway. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Evening Star</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="15e138a339d6e8238a545af61dd42ea2" data-recommend-id="image://15e138a339d6e8238a545af61dd42ea2" data-format="png" data-width="2000" data-height="1125" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Penny's Big Breakaway. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p><em>Penny’s Big Breakaway</em> <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zmzS9vz6h30&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zmzS9vz6h30" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">snuck out earlier this year</a></span> and it’s a great adventure platformer in the mold of a lost Sega Saturn game. It has beautiful visuals and fun arcade-y levels that offer a great mix of retro-fueled nostalgia and modern invention. </p><p><strong>Price:</strong> $18 (40 percent off)</p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="c5a30361b267916fa69893bf3f8797fa" data-recommend-id="image://c5a30361b267916fa69893bf3f8797fa" data-format="jpg" data-width="1200" data-height="672" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows characters from Midnight Suns. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows characters from Midnight Suns. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Firaxis Games</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="c5a30361b267916fa69893bf3f8797fa" data-recommend-id="image://c5a30361b267916fa69893bf3f8797fa" data-format="jpg" data-width="1200" data-height="672" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows characters from Midnight Suns. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p><em>Marvel’s Midnight Suns</em> is <em>XCOM </em>meets <em>Dragon Age</em> with card-based battle mechanics. It sounds overwhelming but it’s <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-midnight-suns-impressions-xcom-firaxis-pc-rpg-1849793171&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-midnight-suns-impressions-xcom-firaxis-pc-rpg-1849793171">sneakily good</a></span> and regularly goes on sale for a steal. If you’re going through Marvel withdraw at the moment this is a great way to get your fix, especially since an actual <em>Blade </em>movie still seems to be in production hell. </p><p><strong>Price:</strong> $10.50 (80 percent off)</p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="2d31b72dfb620a6cf8d80a6869c48cc4" data-recommend-id="image://2d31b72dfb620a6cf8d80a6869c48cc4" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Crash Bandicoot. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Crash Bandicoot. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Activision</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="2d31b72dfb620a6cf8d80a6869c48cc4" data-recommend-id="image://2d31b72dfb620a6cf8d80a6869c48cc4" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Crash Bandicoot. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>There’s no PlayStation 1 <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/crash-bandicoot-5-spyro-crossover-cancelled-activision-1851632213&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/crash-bandicoot-5-spyro-crossover-cancelled-activision-1851632213">without<em> Crash Bandicoot</em></a></span>. Fortunately, the <em>N. Sane Trilogy</em> does a great job of taking the original games and transporting them into an over-the-shoulder 3D format that feels faithful but fresh. </p><p><strong>Price:</strong> $16 (60 percent off)</p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="666e2bb2ca220eeae3b4926c90acf452" data-recommend-id="image://666e2bb2ca220eeae3b4926c90acf452" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Tunic. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Tunic. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Tunic Team</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="666e2bb2ca220eeae3b4926c90acf452" data-recommend-id="image://666e2bb2ca220eeae3b4926c90acf452" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Tunic. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p><em>Tunic </em>is a <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/tunic-xbox-game-pass-zelda-dark-souls-fez-indie-impress-1848668747&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/tunic-xbox-game-pass-zelda-dark-souls-fez-indie-impress-1848668747">twee-looking<em> Zelda</em>-like</a></span> about exploring a paper-crafted world with beautiful atmosphere and music that’s fully of mystery. The game thrives on not explaining anything to you, making the process of uncovering an in-game instruction manual to explain how everything works part of its adventure. It was a strong 2022 GOTY contender that only feels more special years later. </p><p><strong>Price:</strong> $15 (50 percent off)</p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="758df8e90e3e506f7319df4a257641b0" data-recommend-id="image://758df8e90e3e506f7319df4a257641b0" data-format="jpg" data-width="1607" data-height="902" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Dredge. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Dredge. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Black Salt Games</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="758df8e90e3e506f7319df4a257641b0" data-recommend-id="image://758df8e90e3e506f7319df4a257641b0" data-format="jpg" data-width="1607" data-height="902" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Dredge. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p><em>Dredge </em>was a <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dredge-fishing-game-review-life-sim-nintendo-switch-1850284719&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dredge-fishing-game-review-life-sim-nintendo-switch-1850284719">2023 GOTY contender</a></span> that’s finally getting some steeper discounts. It offers an enticing loop of catching fish, fixing up your boat, and exploring the horrors lurking in the depths of the ocean and your nighttime-addled imagination. </p><p><strong>Price:</strong> $15 (40 percent off)</p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="3d8db9f9cc855c428ac8142784838527" data-recommend-id="image://3d8db9f9cc855c428ac8142784838527" data-format="jpg" data-width="1177" data-height="664" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Gravity Rush 2. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Gravity Rush 2. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sony</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="3d8db9f9cc855c428ac8142784838527" data-recommend-id="image://3d8db9f9cc855c428ac8142784838527" data-format="jpg" data-width="1177" data-height="664" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Gravity Rush 2. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>We might never get a new game like <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/gravity-rush-2-the-kotaku-review-1790999758&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/gravity-rush-2-the-kotaku-review-1790999758"><em>Gravity Rush 2</em></a></span> again. One of the last big, imaginative releases from the now-shutdown Japan Studio, it sports the nature-defying acrobatics of the first game in an even more vibrant, beautiful, and immersive world. </p><p><strong>Price:</strong> $10 (50 percent off)</p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="57a8c1c44bce5b761964b48d724272e3" data-recommend-id="image://57a8c1c44bce5b761964b48d724272e3" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Chants of Sennaar." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Chants of Sennaar." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Rundisc</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="57a8c1c44bce5b761964b48d724272e3" data-recommend-id="image://57a8c1c44bce5b761964b48d724272e3" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Chants of Sennaar." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p><em>Chants of Sennaar</em> is an awesome puzzle game that went <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/xbox-game-pass-chants-of-sennaar-puzzle-indie-1851479335&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/xbox-game-pass-chants-of-sennaar-puzzle-indie-1851479335">slightly under-appreciated last year</a></span>. Its colorful, minimalist world has you trying to untangle a made-up language to overcome obstacles and navigate messy political squabbles. It also does a good job of keeping you on track so that its linguistic conundrums never feel too overwhelming. </p><p><strong>Price:</strong> $14 (30 percent off)</p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="219ed79730a158ea8c6dad75e8ff1dc5" data-recommend-id="image://219ed79730a158ea8c6dad75e8ff1dc5" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Blasphemous 2. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Blasphemous 2. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->The Game Kitchen</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="219ed79730a158ea8c6dad75e8ff1dc5" data-recommend-id="image://219ed79730a158ea8c6dad75e8ff1dc5" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows Blasphemous 2. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>The original <em>Blasphemous </em>was part of an early batch of 2D Soulslikes that combined punishing combat with old-school pixel art. The sequel leans more heavily into a Metroidvania formula for a richer overall experience. It’s gorgeous, gore-y, and brutally fun all at once. It also recently got <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/sea-stars-tmnt-remnant-2-roguelike-boss-rush-free-dlc-1851706358&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/sea-stars-tmnt-remnant-2-roguelike-boss-rush-free-dlc-1851706358">a free update</a></span> and paid DLC. </p><p><strong>Price:</strong> $15 (50 percent off)</p></div></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
